      • replay

        @NotNull
PropertyFailure.CounterExample<T> replay()
        Re-run the generator and the property on the GenerationEnvironment corresponding to this counter-example.

        This can be useful for debugging, when this example fails after some previous runs and shrinking, but doesn't fail by itself. This can indicate unnoticed side effects in the generators and properties. Catching PropertyFalsified exception, calling replay and putting some breakpoints might shed some light on the reasons involved.
        Returns:
        a CounterExample with the results from the re-run. If re-run is successful (which also indicates some unaccounted side effects), a CounterExample is returned with an exception cause indicating that fact.

      • getSerializedData

        @NotNull
String getSerializedData()
        Returns:
        the data used for generator to produce this counterexample, serialized into Base64. To be used with PropertyChecker.Parameters.rechecking(java.lang.String).
